ectives on the history of ideas, the history of literary motifs and Goethe's biography.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aGoethe, Johann Wolfgang von. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / German.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies - 1990 - 1999z9783110637830oZDB-23-GLC0 cprintz978348410771740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311092978240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110929782423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110929782/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-GLCc1990d1999